<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="4"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" color="#c0c0c0" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><div><div><font size="4">We hope you have enjoyed the Christmas holidays and we wish you a Happy New Year. &nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Welcome to a new term in Year 2, where we are looking forward to building on the creative, literacy-based curriculum the children have enjoyed so far.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Last term, the children thoroughly enjoyed our ‘Famous People’ and ‘Space’ topic and we were very pleased to see such creativity and imagination both in class and in the children's homework. We know that a lot of time and effort was put in both by the children and the parents and we would like to thank you. Term 2 will equally be fun filled, with new and exciting topics. This term, our main topic will be ‘<b>Islands</b>’- a geography based topic. We endeavour to include as many subjects as possible in our topic to ensure the children are engaged in their learning.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In English, we will be reading a variety of fiction and non-fiction books based on our topic of Islands. From this we will be learn to write within different genres by looking at the layout and textual features. Writing genres covered this term will include <b>Recounts, Non Chronological Reports, Poetry and Story Writing</b>. &nbsp;As well as covering Spelling, Punctuation and Grammar in our daily lessons, the children will have a separate lesson dedicated to these areas.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Continuing on from last term, children will also take part in daily guided reading sessions to help develop their reading fluency and comprehension, as well as daily Phonics based on the Letters and Sounds programme. Continuing to develop the children’s phonics knowledge is essential to their reading and spelling.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In <b>Mathematics </b>we will work on<b>:</b></font></div><div><ul><li><span style="font-size: large;">Understanding what division is and learning methods to help us solve problems relating to division</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Recognise, find, write and name different fractions. In addition to this, the children will be finding fraction amounts of given numbers</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Use standard measurement to estimate and measure height, mass, temperature and capacity. Furthermore, children will be applying their knowledge of previously taught methods to solve problems based around measurement</span></li></ul></div><div><font size="4">In addition to the following topics, we will be continuing to secure our knowledge and understanding of place value. Furthermore, we will be continually revisiting calculation methods taught within Term 1, such as the numberline and column method for addition and subtraction and the numberline method for multiplication. &nbsp;Through various starters, we will also be continuing to develop the children's mental maths skills.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4"><b>The Integrated Curriculum</b> <b>(Topic)</b> will focus on <b>Islands</b>. During this topic, we will be drawing comparisons between islands in Malaysia and in the UK. We will be doing this by:</font></div><div><ul><li><span style="font-size: large;">Understanding what an island is&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Locating different countries, cities and oceans on a world map through using atlases</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Understanding the difference between a human feature and a physical feature</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Locating famous human features, such as the Petronas Towers, London Eye.&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Using maps to name and locate physical features, such as mountains, rivers.</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Using compass points for directions</span></li></ul></div><div><font size="4">At the end of the unit, the children will be given an unlabelled map of a island in either the UK or Malaysia. From the children's learning from the term, they must decide if it is an island in the UK or Malaysia.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In <b>Science</b> we will be looking at <b>Living Things and their Habitats</b>. Within this topic, we will be:</font></div><div><ul><li><span style="font-size: large;">Exploring and comparing the differences between things that are living, dead and things that have never been alive.&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Identifying and naming different habitats</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Beginning to name different plants and animals within particular habitats</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Understanding that most living things live in habitats which are suited to the basic needs of the plants and animals that live within it</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Understanding that plants and animals depend on each other</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Describing how animals obtain their food from either plants and/or other animals through looking at simple food chain</span></li></ul></div><div><font size="4">In <b>Computing</b> we will be continuing with our developing our coding skills on the iPads. In addition to this, we will be learning how to use our school gmail accounts and most importantly how to be safe when online. Furthermore, we will be looking at how we can use search engines, such as Google, to easily search for information.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4">&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4">In <b>Art and Design Technology</b> we will be looking at:</font></div><div><ul><li><span style="font-size: large;">Designing and creating our own habitats</span></li><li><span style="font-size: large;">Research, designing, creating and evaluating our own boats to escape from a tropical island</span></li></ul></div><div><font size="4">&nbsp;</font></div><div><span style="font-size: large;">In <b>Modern Foreign Languages</b> children will either learn Spanish or Mandarin at their appropriate ability level.&nbsp;</span></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In Term 2, the Mandarin lessons in Year 2 will be covering the topics of ‘Colours’, ‘Clothing’ and Chinese New Year. We will continue to reinforce their listening and speaking skills and start to work on their reading and writing skills. The heritage group will be focusing on the passage “Xiao Gou Fei Chang Ke Ai” (Cute Puppy) and “Zhe Ge Gong Yuan Zhen Re Nao” (The Park Is Very Lively). As well as this, they will be extended further by learning a wider range of vocabulary and writing descriptions of characters.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In Spanish, the children will cover the following topics: The body, family (including descriptions), Carnival, Valentine’s Day, clothes and fashion, my bedroom, Father’s Day, Easter, as well as using stories and continuing to revise previously taught topics (maths and phonics).</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In addition, our Malaysian children will continue to have weekly Bahasa lessons. This term they will be learning the numbers and colours.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In <b>Music</b>, children will continue with their choice of instrument from the string family (violin, viola or cello) as part of the Primary Instrumental Programme (PIPs). Children learn their chosen instrument in a small group where they benefit from the interaction with specialist teachers.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In addition to PIPs lessons, children will continue with their weekly music lessons led by our talented music department. Topics will include:</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4"><b>Topic 1 “Feel the pulse” (Exploring pulse and rhythm)</b></font></div><div><font size="4">In this unit, the children focus on pulse / beat and rhythm through various activities, including identification of the beat in music of varying tempo and meter, recalling and copying rhythm patterns, creating rhythm patterns based on words and phrases and using beat and rhythm to create an accompaniment to a song.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4"><b>Topic 2 “Taking off” (Exploring pitch)</b></font></div><div><font size="4">In this unit, the children focus on pitch through various activities, including listening and identification of pitch changes, moving in response to pitch changes, singing and playing simple melodies, and creating simple melodies of their own using graphic scores and notation.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In every lesson the children are constantly developing their singing voices, listening skills, physical skills and aural memory through different activities, depending on the elements focus of the topics covered in the term. Furthermore, the children will also enjoy opportunities to sing, listen, perform and compose music linked to their themes in class.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">In <b>Physical Education (PE)</b>, the children will have two hours of PE a week with an additional session for swimming.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4">&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4">In their PE lessons, over the course of Term 2 and the start of Term 3, the Year 2 children will take part in the following activities: &nbsp;unihoc, Invasion Games (rugby), Outdoor Adventure Activities (OAA), using the climbing wall, gymnastics, racket skills and striking and fielding activities. &nbsp;These activities will be rotated throughout the term, so that all groups take part in all activities. The children will require a hat for PE, as some of these activities will take place on the Primary roof space.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Swimming lessons will be in accordance to the children’s ability. During the first part of term, children will continue to work towards the whole school swimming awards, which can be found displayed in the primary canteen. In the second part of the term, children will be preparing for the swimming gala.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">To continue to develop our children as <b>Confident Speakers</b>, we will be continuing to work on increasing our confidence when speaking in front of groups or the class. Where possible, teachers will allow children the opportunity to present in front of their peers. Furthermore, this term, Year 2 will produce a whole year group performance, which will be held for parents on the 23rd of March. Further details, when available, will be added to the Parent Portal calendar.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">As a reminder for <b>Homework</b>, children will continue to be given a weekly English/literacy activity to complete and a maths activity. At times, this homework may be set on Education City. If homework is set on Education City or online, we will notify you through the class portal blogs. &nbsp;Also, children will receive weekly phonics homework, which is based on the sounds and tricky words they have been learning in class. In addition, children may be given a topic activity to complete as well. During Year 2 the children will be expected to do some research-based homework.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Like last term, each week children will be given the chance to go to the library to borrow a book. In addition, the class teacher will be sending out reading packs at the end of each week. We encourage daily reading with your child. Regular reading and enjoying stories with your child is invaluable and extremely rewarding.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4"><b>Communication</b></font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Each Year 2 class will continue to share with you what is happening in class via the class portal blogs. Any changes to normal school routine or important dates/events will be shared via the school calendar. Although a notification e-mail may be sent, we encourage parents to check the Parent Portal calendar regularly.</font></div><div><font size="4">&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4">Finally, I would like to remind all parents that for safeguarding purposes, all adults <b>must wear their identification tags at all</b> <b>times within school</b>. Also, if your child is to be collected by someone else, please do inform us in advance.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">I hope this letter gives you a brief insight into what your child will be learning this term. As always, if you have any questions or concerns please contact your class teacher as a first point of contact. We encourage you to ask your child each day about what they did at school and most importantly what they have learnt.</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">The Year 2 team would like to thank all parents for their continued support.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Kind regards,</font></div><div><font size="4"><b>Year 2 Team</b></font></div><div><font size="4"><b><br></b></font></div><div><font size="4">Christine McNicol (Year Group Leader) &amp; Mr Freddy</font></div><div><font size="4">christine.mcnicol@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Paul Jones and Miss Minky</font></div><div><font size="4">paul.jones@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Sophie Moore and Ms Carrie</font></div><div><font size="4">sophie.moore@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Shaun Wilson &amp; Miss Hope&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="4">shaun.wilson@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><font size="4"><br></font></div><div><font size="4">Kimberley Webb and Miss Madeline</font></div><div><font size="4">kimberley.webb@britishschool.edu.my</font></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font size="4"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div></div></span></font></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font><font class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">&nbsp;</font></div>]]></td>
